Step 1: Compute the average total assets.
• Initial Total Assets = 16,000,000.00  
• End Total Assets = 21,098,887.48  
• Average Total Assets = (16,000,000.00 + 21,098,887.48) / 2 = 18,549,443.74

Step 2: Use the Net Profit from the income statement.
• Net Profit = 56,497.85

Step 3: Calculate the ROA.
• ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%  
• ROA = (56,497.85 / 18,549,443.74) × 100% ≈ 0.3044%

Rounded to two decimal places, the ROA is approximately 0.30%.

Thus, the answer is:
{
  "solution": {'Return on Assets (ROA)': '0.30%'}
}
